Package: git-ftp
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, curl (>= 7.15.5), git-core (>= 1.7), grep (>= 2.5.1)
Description: Git powered FTP client written as shell script.
 git-ftp is a shell script for uploading Git tracked files to a FTP server. By
 default, it uploads only those files which have changed since the last upload.
 .
 This saves time and bandwith. You can even play with different branches. See
 manpage for more options.
